<H3> <TI>   Attempted Robbery at Chemical Defense Academy Foiled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2112112393 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 21 Dec 
93 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2112112393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Zaynetdinov report: ```Robbery of the Century.' </F>
Almost''] 
  [Text] The ``robbery of the century'' could have occurred 
in Moscow, had help not arrived. Around 0500 seven criminals 
attacked a training battalion at the Russian Federation Defense 
Ministry's Chemical Defense Academy. 
  Colonel Yuriy Reshetnik, a staffer at the Russian Federation 
MVD [Ministry of Internal Affairs] Public Relations Center, gave 
the details. The attackers beat up the duty officer and a 
soldier. The bandits then took their keys to the ``armory'' 
[oruzheyka]. But no weapons were stolen--the military arrived in 
time. 

</TEXT>

