<H3> <TI>   Novovoronezh Nuclear Plant on Brink of Shutdown </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1612201593 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1316 GMT 
16 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD1612201593 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Novovoronezh nuclear plant is close to being 
partially or completely shut down. It is one of nine plants 
providing lighting and heating for Russia. Its contribution to 
the country's power system is 12 percent. In the central and 
black earth region the Novovoronezh plant provides 75 percent of 
the power needed by the region. Systematic nonpayments by 
consumers are the reason for the possible shutdown: the 
nonpayments slow down the reconstruction and modernization of 
the station's power sets. There are not sufficient funds to 
improve safety guarantees. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

