<H3> <TI>   Official Says Government `Adheres' to Arms Trade Norms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2112123293 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1100 GMT 21 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> WS2112123293 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a briefing for Ukrainian and foreign 
reporters on 21 December, Ukrainian Deputy Foreign Minister 
Borys Tarasyuk, chairman of the national Committee for 
Disarmament, said: The Ukrainian Government adheres to 
international norms, principles, and standards, and observes all 
sanctions imposed by the United Nations in the issues of arms 
trade. Ukraine does not sell arms to either the Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia, the South African Republic, or Iraq. 
With regard to selling certain types of arms to Iran, Ukraine 
is pursuing its own economic interests and observes security 
principles. Borys Tarasyuk underlined that Ukraine had never 
sold sea-launched guided missiles to Iran. According to the 
Ukrainian diplomat, taking advantage of the imperfection of the 
system of control exercised by the Coordinating Committee for 
Multilateral Exports Controls, middlemen manage to ship arms, 
products, and technologies to the states under ban. 

</TEXT>

