<H3> <TI>   Fault Causes Emergency Shutdown at Zaporozhye AES </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1412153493 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1200 GMT 14 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD1412153493 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The information center of the Zaporozhye AES 
reported that the first generating set went temporarily out of 
order last night. It was deactivated by the emergency shutdown 
system because of a fault in the water make-up unit in one of 
the turbine generators. The reactor plant capacity thus became 
ineffective. The fault was quickly rectified, and the generating 
set was switched on again. At the same time, the information 
center reports, the civil defense alarm sounded while the 
technical staff was being informed of the incident. The cause 
of the alarm is being investigated. The incident at the AES 
poses no danger to the safety of its personnel or the 
population. Background radiation remains within the norm. 

</TEXT>

