<H3> <TI>   `17 November' Reportedly Sought Funds, Arms From Iran </TI></H3>
<H4>   Iranian Embassy Denies Report </H4>
<F P=102> LD2812144193 Tehran IRNA in English 1418 GMT 28 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD2812144193 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Athens, Dec 28, IRNA -- The Islamic Republic Embassy 
Tuesday dismissed an Italian press report claiming that the 
Greek terrorist group `17 November' recently held secret talks 
in Tehran. The embassy described the report as "totally baseless 
and lies." 
  "The report is absolutely baseless and completely lies and 
false. It is a wicked attempt to harm the very close and 
friendly relations between Greece and Iran," an Iranian Embassy 
source told IRNA. 

