<F P=102> MB3012102393 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1005 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> MB3012102393 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Dec 30 SAPA -- A caller identifying 
himself as a commander of the Azanian National Liberation Army 
(Azanla) on Thursday claimed responsibility for an explosion 
which damaged a block of flats in Port Elizabeth's Swartkops 
industrial area shortly after midnight on Tuesday. There were 
no injuries. 
  Shortly after the Tuesday blast, police found large amounts 
of explosives in several places at a block of flats in Algoa 
Park, about 15km from Swartkops. Officers said at the time 
police were investigating a possible link between the blast and 
the explosives seized. The caller said the sabotage was part of 
Azanla's campaign for the complete liberation of all Azanians. 
"The struggle will continue until we are all free." 
  There was no way of independently confirming the caller was 
from Azanla, armed wing of the Black Consciousness Movement of 
Azania, which has rejected the constitutional deal reached in 
negotiations at Kempton Park. 

