<H3> <TI>   Cathedral, Mosques, Market Bombed in South </TI></H3>
<H4>   Grenade in Bonifacio Market Kills 10 </H4>
<F P=102> BK2912020093 Manila MANILA BULLETIN in English 25 Dec 93 p 14 </F>
<F P=103> BK2912020093 </F>
<F P=104>  Manila MANILA BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By T. Rimando] </F>
  [Text] Pagadian City -- At least 10 persons were blasted 
to death, while some 25 others were seriously wounded when a 
grenade believed hurled by members of the New People's Army 
(NPA) exploded in an overcrowded public market in Barangay 
[village] Bagumbang, Bonifacio town, Misamis Occidental at 2 
p.m. yesterday. 
  A sketchy police report received here said six died on the 
spot, while four others expired on the way to hospitals. 
  The report identified only three of the fatalities. They 
were Inday Monteramos, Undo Saguin, and a certain "Dodong." 
  The wounded were taken to government hospitals in Ozamiz 
City 
and Tangub City, some 40 and 25 kilometers, respectively, north 
of Bonifacio town. 
  Misamis Occidental Representative Hilario Ramiro Jr., a 
resident of Ozamiz City, led government hospital staff in 
attending to the wounded, some of whom were given a 50/50 chance 
to survive. 

</TEXT>

