<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> PHILIPPINES </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communist Spokesman Rejects Boncayao Brigade </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Real' Brigade To Be Revived </H4>
<F P=102> BK2712113793 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 27 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> BK2712113793 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 27 Dec 93 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Tagalog </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The breakaway groups of the Communist Party of the 
Philippines [CPP] have been accused of deception because of 
their continued use of the name Alex Boncayao Brigade [ABB]. 
This accusation came from Gregorio Rosal, alias Comrade Roger, 
spokesman for the Militor Glor Command. 
  [Begin correspondent Norie Temblor recording] In an 
exclusive 
interview with GMA-7 at Sierra Madre, Rosal said that the 
breakaway factions lost the right to use the name Alex Boncayao 
Brigade after they broke off ties with the Communist Party of 
the Philippines. It will be recalled that many CPP units headed 
by the NCR [National Capital Region] regional party committee 
cut their ties with CPP Chairman Jose Maria Sison. In this 
connection, Rosal said they will reactivate the real Alex 
Boncayao Brigade to counter the impostor ABB. 
  Regarding the coming peace talks, Rosal revealed that the 
CPP 
remains open to the peace talks. In the meantime, Rosal called 
on Ramos to give more attention to the important issues in the 
peace talks rather than focusing on the issue of giving Sison a 
passport. 
  On the ongoing cease-fire, Rosal disclosed that they have 
not 
committed any violations. 
  Meanwhile, government troops continue their intensive 
surveillance of suspected New People's Army camps. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

