Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Communist Party of the Philippines [CPP] has 
strongly criticized the continued operation of the Alex Boncayao 
Brigade [ABB] in Metro Manila. According to Gregorio Rosal, 
alias Comrade Roger, head of the CPP Information Bureau, this 
liquidation squad was dismantled and disarmed in December last 
year. He reiterated that the current ABB is illegal and is not 
recognized by the hierarchy of the CPP-NPA [New People's Army]. 
It is allegedly supported by the breakaway group of the Metro 
Manila-Rizal Regional Committee under the leadership of Felimon 
Lagman, alias Carlos Forte. The ABB was recently involved in 
the robbery of a truck loaded with rice in Binondo, Manila. 

