<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regional Guerrilla Activity Roundup 22 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2312211393 </F>
<F P=103> PA2312211393 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on regional guerrilla activities and clashes with 
government military units monitored through 22 December. Source 
is cited in parentheses following each item. 
<H5>  Colombia </H5>
  The Army Command in Cali announced on 21 December that 
Alvaro 
Martinez, commander of the leftist Revolutionary Armed Forces of 
Colombia, FARC, 6th Front died in a clash with Army forces in 
the rural region of Tulua, in southwestern Valle del Cauca 
Department. (Paris AFP in Spanish 1346 GMT 21 Dec 93) 
  Five policemen died and five others were wounded and four 
are 
missing as a result of a guerrilla ambush carried out in La 
Chorrera, Bolivar Municipality, in south Cauca. Cartagena also 
has been the target of terrorism: Three urban bus stops were 
dynamited on the morning of 22 December by National Liberation 
Army units. (Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 
in Spanish 1730 GMT 22 Dec 93) 
<H5>  Ecuador </H5>
  Ecuadoran police Colonels Milton Molina and Jorge Poveda 
have 
reported that elite police units captured three alleged FARC 
guerrillas in the Amazon Jungle region. The arrests took place 
after the ambush by a terrorist FARC column against an Ecuadoran 
police-military force sailing on the Putumayo River. (Paris AFP 
in Spanish 0141 GMT 21 Dec 93) 
<H5>  Nicaragua </H5>
  Three peasants were murdered and a minor injured as a result 
of terrorist acts carried out by recontra groups of the 3-80 
Northern Front in Matagalpa and Jinotega Departments. One of 
the peasants was killed in El Jobo, near Wiwili; and the other 
two in Bocay, Jinotega Department. (Managua EL NUEVO DIARIO in 
Spanish 22 Dec 93 p 8) 
  Army General Humberto Ortega reported today that 487 
persons, 
including irregular forces, military, and civilians, have died 
so far this year as a result of the violence in northern 
Nicaragua where up to November there had been 247 clashes. 
(Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2124 GMT 22 Dec 93) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

