<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> PERU </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Insurgent Activities 11 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2812222793 </F>
<F P=103> PY2812222793 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Following are reports on insurgent 
activities in Peru compiled from Peruvian papers published on 11 
December. 
  The National Counterterrorism Directorate on 18 November 
arrested Shining Path "terrorist" Edison Tomas Zarate Untiveros, 
23, in Lima's La Victoria District. He carried ammunition, 
"subversive" literature, and handwritten notes. He had sought 
refuge in Argentina, from where he returned to Peru at the 
request of People's Aid of Peru to head its defense department's 
military command and to prepare car bombs for the organization. 
Zarate reportedly was involved in car bombs that exploded 
between September and November. Police also arrested six other 
Shining Path "terrorists" during operations in Lima between 24 
November and 2 December. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 11 Dec 93 
p A16) 

</TEXT>

