<H3> <TI>   Firm Damaged, Guard Wounded in Car Bomb Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA3012031193 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 0245 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> PA3012031193 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Carlos Enrique Villarreal] </F>
  [Text] The explosion of a car bomb has caused much 
destruction at China de Maquinaria y Equipos del Peru, a firm 
located on block No. 11, East Javier Prado Avenue in La Victoria 
District. 
  According to initial reports, one person was wounded -- the 
security guard of the firm in question. A paramedic unit of 
Peru's volunteer fire service are treating the guard. Many 
policemen are guarding the area. Approximately 60 percent of 
the installations of China de Maquinaria and Equipos del Peru 
was destroyed. In addition, nearby buildings belonging to auto 
dealerships were also affected. 
  A light blue Volkswagen was used in this attack. Its license 
plate number is DI-8009. 

