<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mosad Linked With Plan To Kill Lebanese Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3012072693 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0615 GMT 30 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3012072693 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The newspaper AL-SAFIR reports that Lebanese 
security authorities have uncovered a terrorist ring working for 
the Israeli intelligence agency, Mosad. The ring planned to 
assassinate high-ranking Lebanese officials to destabilize the 
country and embarrass Syria ahead of the Syrian-U.S. summit. 
  AL-SAFIR reports that one ring member who was arrested 
recently was tasked with assassinating a high-ranking official. 
The authorities have also foiled a plan to assassinate a 
minister and a senior military official. 
  Citing well-informed sources, AL-SAFIR says the Israel 
agencies and another, non-Israeli, party have drawn up a plan to 
weaken Syria's position. They want to weaken President 
al-Asad's position ahead of the Geneva summit with President 
Clinton. So they planned to embarrass him in Lebanon. 
  This information follows Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin's recent visit to the occupied border strip and his veiled 
threats against Lebanon and Syria. 

</TEXT>

