<H3> <TI>   Four Sentinels, Passerby Killed in Asyut Area 26 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2612112593 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1055 GMT 26 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC2612112593 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 26 Dec (MENA)--Four police sentinels from the 
al-Qusiyah district force in the Asyut Governorate were killed 
today when unidentified men opened fire at them. In reporting 
this, a security official in the Interior Ministry said that 
citizen Na'im Bakhit Hanna, who happened to be on the scene, was 
also hit by the indiscriminate firing and succumbed to his 
wounds. The source said that the criminals fired at the four 
sentinels as they were going to work at the police post in Bani 
Qurrah and seized their weapons. The commanders of the Asyut 
Security Directorate, the Public Security, the State Security 
intelligence, and experts of the criminal laboratory went to the 
scene of the incident to investigate. Security forces are 
searching the area to arrest the criminals. 

</TEXT>

