<H3> <TI>   `Islamic Group' Attacks Tour Bus, Wounds 9 Austrians </TI></H3>
<H4>   Islamic Group Claims Attack </H4>
<F P=102> NC2812160193 Paris AFP in English 1343 GMT 28 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC2812160193 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, Dec 28 (AFP)--An underground Islamic 
fundamentalist group in Egypt on Tuesday [28 December] claimed 
responsibility for the bomb and gun attack on a Cairo tour bus 
that wounded eight Austrians. 
  The al-Jama'ah al-Islamiyah [Islamic Group] said Monday's 
attack in Misr al-Qadimah, after which the assailants shot and 
wounded eight Egyptians while fleeing the scene, was "in 
retaliation for the recent executions" of several al-Jama'ah 
members. 
  Al-Jama'ah claimed responsibility in a statement sent to the 
Arabic daily AL-HAYAH, which is published in several capitals. 
  At least 261 people have been killed since March 1992, when 
Islamic militants stepped up their violent campaign aimed at 
toppling the secular government of President Husni Mubarak. 
  The government has rounded up hundreds of suspects and 
hanged 
23 Moslem fundamentalists since June. 

</TEXT>

