<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Shaykh Ahmad Yasin, the Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] spiritual leader, said this morning that 
his movement would accept a cease-fire with Israel provided that 
the use of firearms against Palestinians stops. Yasin added 
that Hamas will not stop its activities until the Jewish 
settlements in the Gaza Strip are evacuated. Shaykh Yasin made 
the remarks at a meeting this morning with Knesset Member Talib 
al-Sani' at the Ramla Prison hospital where Yasin is being 
imprisoned. [passage omitted with al-Sani' remarks] 
