<H3> <TI>   Fatah-Uprising Operation Against Ship in Eilat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2512160493 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1515 GMT 25 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> JN2512160493 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 25 Dec (SANA)--The Palestine National 
Liberation Movement, Fatah [the Uprising], has announced that 
one of its groups has detonated explosive and incendiary devices 
inside the Israeli ship Jrush Shalom [name as received] while it 
was docked at Eilat port. 
  A statement issued by the movement today said the explosion 
caused a fire in the ship and that heavy clouds of poisonous 
gases were leaked as a result of the fire in the ship's cargo of 
poisonous materials. The ship's cargo was due to be unloaded 
into the warehouses of the enemy's army. 
  The statement said 11 sailors were injured, and the group 
that carried out the operation returned safely. 

</TEXT>

