<H3> <TI>   Intifadah Figures Since Agreement With PLO Publicized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2912190893 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1800 GMT 29 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> TA2912190893 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Since the signing of the agreement with the PLO 
there has been an increase in the number of stone-throwing and 
petrol bomb incidents and a decrease in the number of shooting 
and stabbing incidents: 180 petrol bombs were thrown in the 
three months preceding the agreement, whereas 315 were thrown 
since the signing of the agreement on 13 September. On the 
other hand there has been a sharp fall in the number of shooting 
and stabbing incidents. These figures were relayed from the 
prime minister's bureau to Likud Chairman Binyamin Netanyahu at 
the latter's request. The Likud claims that the government is 
hiding the figures in order to justify the claim that the 
intifadah has subsided. 

</TEXT>

