<H3> <TI>   Fatah-Uprising Claims Cross-Border Raid </TI></H3>
<H4>   IDF Kills 3 `Terrorist' Infiltrators on Lebanese Border </H4>
<F P=102> TA3012053593 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 30 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> TA3012053593 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alan Ben-'Ami] </F>
  [Text] The Israeli Army spokesman has just issued some 
very brief details about a clash between Israeli soldiers and 
terrorists on the border with Lebanon in the eastern sector of 
the security zone. According to the first details, three 
terrorists were killed in the clash as they tried to cross the 
border fence near the village of Arajah in the eastern sector. 
It is approximately in the area of Kibbutz Dan in the Upper 
Galilee region. 
  Israeli soldiers were alerted to the infiltration attempt, 
arrived quickly at the scene and opened fire at the terrorists, 
killing them. There are no reports of any casualties on the 
Israeli side, and apparently the head of Northern Command, Major 
General Yitzhaq Mordekhay, has arrived at the scene to check out 
the situation, and has already praised the action of the 
soldiers, and particularly their speedy arrival at the site of 
the infiltration. 

</TEXT>

