Document Type:JPRS 
Document Title:Terrorism 

</HEADER>

<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   7 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah-Uprising Claims Cross-Border Raid </TI></H3>
<H4>   Fatah-The Uprising Claims Settlement Raid </H4>
<F P=102> NC3012094693 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0920 GMT 30 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3012094693 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fatah-the Uprising today claimed responsibility for 
the infiltration of the Lebanese-Israeli border by three 
fedayeen who were killed in a confrontation with Israeli forces 
near al-Majidiyah. In a statement released today, Fatah-the 
Uprising said the fedayeen group raided the Dan settlement at 
dawn today using machine guns and rockets and clashed with the 
settlement guards for two hours, killing or wounding several 
Israelis. 
  Citing security sources, REUTER reported that the three 
fedayeen crossed the border and that the Israelis discovered 
them near the village of al-Majidiyah on the Lebanese-Israeli 
border. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

