<F P=101> LIBYA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Comment on al-Kikhya Disappearance </TI></H3>
<H4>   Egypt Says Government Not Cooperating </H4>
<F P=102> NC2512174493 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 25 Dec 
93 </F>

<F P=103> NC2512174493 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A responsible Egyptian source said today that the 
visit to Libya by Usamah al-Baz, director of President Mubarak's 
Office for Political Affairs, has not achieved any positive 
results on the fate of Libyan dissident Mansur al-Kikhya, who 
disappeared in Cairo. The same source added that al-Baz received 
no gesture of cooperation from Libyan officials on this issue. 
He noted that al-Kikhya's disappearance is now being handled at 
the security level pending the outcome of an investigation into 
the incident. The source said that Egypt and its people do not 
tolerate anyone harming Egypt's security or its guests. 
  So far, no official statement has been issued on the results 
of al-Baz's visit to Libya. Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
said Monday that Egypt's stance on the issue will be determined 
by the outcome of the security agencies' investigations. 
  After al-Baz's return on Tuesday, some deputies asked the 
government to announce the outcome of his mission to Libya and 
the results of investigations. 
  An Arab diplomatic source has clarified that the Egyptian 
Government's silence on al-Baz's visit shows its dissatisfaction 
with Libya and its conviction about that government's 
involvement in al-Kikhya's abduction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-60835 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jptot001__l94083" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   JPRS-TOT-94-001-L </AU>
