<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   7 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> SUDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Sources Criticize US Embassy's `Provocation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2712091993 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0900 GMT 27 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC2712091993 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 27 Dec (MENA)--Sudanese diplomatic sources 
have criticized what they called provocation by the U.S. Embassy 
in Khartoum, which presented awards to the families of Sudanese 
citizens in appreciation of their efforts during the U.S. 
humanitarian aid operations, despite a Sudanese criminal court 
condemning these activities. 
  The official newspaper AL-INQADH AL-WATANI cited the sources 
as saying that the Sudanese Government does not want to respond 
to the U.S. provocation and has agreed to form a committee to 
discuss the trial's legal procedures. 

