<H3> <TI>   Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given </TI></H3>
<H4>   Details of Kidnapping From School </H4>
<F P=102> LD2312155493 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1500 
GMT 23 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2312155493 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vyacheslav Bondarenko] </F>
  [Text] Rostov-on-Don, 23 Dec -- At approximately 1135 [0835 
GMT] today, four armed bandits in bulletproof jackets and 
camouflage uniforms and armed with Kalashnikov automatic rifles 
burst into the ninth "C" form of Rostov's School No. 25 which is 
located practically in the city center. After firing into the 
ceiling, the criminals seized a female teacher and 12 
schoolchildren and led them out to a bus standing outside the 
school. The bus was then driven by a driver, also taken 
hostage, in the direction of a military camp. 
  One of a number of servicemen who began negotiations with 
the 
kidnappers was himself taken hostage. The kidnappers demanded a 
helicopter and crew and talked about "Georgia-Makhachkala-Iran" 
as a preliminary route. 
  According to unsubstantiated data, the terrorists have 
released one of the female pupils. They have called for the 
oblast's administrative head, Vladimir Chub, to take part in 
negotiations. Negotiations are continuing. 

</TEXT>

