<F P=106> ["Urgent" item by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Excerpts] Moscow December 24 TASS -- Bad weather prevented 
the Mi-8 helicopter of the Russian Air Force where terrorists 
are staying with a group of children taken hostage from flying 
to Makhachkala, the capital of the Russian Republic of 
Daghestan, bordering on Azerbaijan on the Caspian Sea, TASS 
learned from the press centre of the Russian Air Force which 
added that kidnappers planned to refuel in Makhachkala and fly 
to Iran. 
