<H3> <TI>   Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hijackers Instructed To Release Hostages, Surrender </H4>
<F P=102> LD2512100193 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0924 GMT 
25 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2512100193 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As an ITAR-TASS correspondent was told by the head 
of the operational headquarters of the Russian Government, First 
Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets, today, on behalf of the 
Russian Government, an ultimatum was issued to the terrorists at 
Mineralnyye Vody airport. 
  The essence of the ultimatum boils down to the following: 
The 
hostages must be released immediately. The terrorists are 
instructed to surrender under a guarantee of personal safety. 
It has also been stated that their actions have given rise to a 
sharp protest among the Russian population. 

</TEXT>

