<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   7 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given </TI></H3>
<H4>   Sketches of Hijackers Released </H4>
<F P=102> LD2512145093 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1438 GMT 25 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD2512145093 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Excerpts] Moscow December 25 TASS -- Terrorists who are 
staying with hostages aboard a helicopter in the Mineralnyye 
Vody airport said they will take off after dark. The kidnappers 
are still holding up three boys, a bus driver and two pilots. 
  As soon as weathermen announced that the weather permitted 
flight, the terrorists ordered the helicopter to be tugged by a 
tractor to a remote runway. [passage omitted] 
  The four terrorists have not been identified yet. Officials 
said the computer sketches of them are available and a photofit 
picture of one of the kidnappers, made with the help of the 
teenager hostages and their teacher which were freed on Friday 
(one boy was freed Saturday morning) in return for a $10 million 
ransom, was shown on Russian television. 
  Officials hope that some of the televiewers will be able to 
identify the terrorists and supply additional data that may help 
to free the remaining hostages. [passage omitted] 
  ITAR-TASS correspondent in Rostov-on-Don, where nine 
teenagers and their teacher were kidnapped on Thursday, quoted 
the school principal as saying that the terrorists declared that 
they all were AIDS-infected and are going abroad for medical 
treatment. They also promised the hostages to give them money 
and take them abroad. 
  The principal, Valentina Fedoseyeva, said that "the children 
burst into laughter when three masked men armed with assault 
rifles burst into their class." They thought it was a joke 
staged by their military instructor and only after the attackers 
fired three rounds into the ceiling did the children realise it 
was serious. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

