<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 25 Dec (ITAR-TASS) -- After a tractor towed 
the helicopter with the terrorists and hostages to another 
runway at the Mineralnyye Vody airport today, another schoolboy, 
Zhenya Mezhuyev, was released. Thus two boys, the bus driver, 
and the helicopter's two pilots are still on board. The 
terrorists have declared they intend to leave Mineralnyye Vody 
when darkness sets in. [passage omitted] 
  The terrorists promise to release the two boys remaining on 
board, having set as a condition that Valentina Petrenko, 
personal envoy of the Russian foreign minister, should be taken 
on board. [passage omitted] 
  It is not excluded that after flying to Baku the terrorists 
will try to land in the mountains where it is possible that 
accomplices await them. 

</TEXT>

