Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After two hours' flight, the helicopter carrying the 
terrorists and hostages returned to Mineralnyye Vody airport. 
Here is our correspondent Valeriy Kuts. 
  [Kuts, in progress as heard] ...by Moscow time, the Mi-8TM 
helicopter with the terrorists and hostages on board took off, 
circled the airport and town several times, and headed off for 
the town of Makhachkala, but because of heavy icing, the 
helicopter had to return to the airport at the town of 
Mineralnyye Vody, where it landed at 0240 Moscow time [2340 
GMT]. Evidently officials of law and order bodies will once 
more attempt to make contact with the criminals at dawn in order 
to establish their further plans. Valeriy Kuts, information 
service. 

