<F P=102> AU2612170193 Paris AFP in English 1650 GMT 26 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU2612170193 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Rostov-on-Don, Russia, Dec 26 (AFP) -- Gunmen 
freed Sunday three of the five hostages they were holding at the 
southern Russia airport of Mineralnyye Vody but took off with 
the two pilots of their commandeered helicopter, officials in 
Rostov-on-Don said. 
  The four gunmen freed the last two schoolboys and a 
busdriver 
they were holding, at around 7:00 p.m. (1600 GMT). The 
helicopter then took off for Makhachkala, capital of the Russian 
republic of Dagestan on the Caspian Sea, a two-hour flight. 
  The officials said the information came from the crisis 
center in Mineralnyye Vody. They did not say if concessions had 
been made to win these releases. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

