<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   7 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given </TI></H3>
<H4>   ITAR-TASS Identifies Hijackers </H4>
<F P=102> LD2712102293 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0933 
GMT 27 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2712102293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Makhachkala, 27 Dec -- All four terrorists who 
kidnapped hostages in Rostov-on-Don on 23 December have been 
identified. The leader of the gang is Arslan Kasimov, born in 
1945, a native of Azerbaijan, who has a criminal record. 
Abdulgafar Abduzhalimov, a native of Tashkent, born in 1972, is 
a fifth-year student at the faculty of applied mechanics of 
Tashkent University. Anatoliy Mikheyev, born in 1949, a native 
of Sverdlovsk, Russia, is a navigator by profession and was 
discharged from the Air Force for drunkenness; recently he has 
been unemployed. The fourth thug is Marat Kauzbekov, born in 
1974, native of Tashkent, a Kazakh and second-year student at 
Tashkent Institute of Architecture. 
  Nearly all of the $10 million handed over to the terrorists 
has been recovered, except for a small sum which, according to 
gang leader Arslan Kasimov, was thrown out of the helicopter 
over Chechen territory. 

</TEXT>

