<H3> <TI>   Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Certain Organization' Helped Hijack </H4>
<F P=102> LD2812121993 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 28 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2812121993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The INTERFAX agency reports that the terrorist 
hijackers captured in Makhachkala yesterday are still in 
Dagestan. They are being held in remand cells and will be 
transferred to Rostov-on-Don in the near future. 
  An Interior Ministry official reports that during 
interrogation it emerged that the terrorists carefully planned 
their action. In particular, they thoroughly reconnoitered the 
airports at Georgiyevsk and Stravropol. Some experts think that 
if the criminals had managed to land at the intended point on 
the border with Chechnya, there would have been very little 
chance of catching them. 
  Moreover, it has emerged that during one of the 
interrogation 
sessions former military pilot Anatoliy Mikheyev said there was 
a certain organization behind the groups' actions and that it 
had helped plan the crime. 

</TEXT>

