<H3> <TI>   Grey Wolves Party Holds First Conference </TI></H3>
<H4>   History Professor Elected Chairman </H4>
<F P=102> NC2712143993 Baku TURAN in English 1243 GMT 27 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC2712143993 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, December 27 (TURAN)--At the recent founders' 
conference of the Boz Gurd Party, Bahdiar Ahmedov, a professor 
of history from the Baku University, was elected chairman of the 
party yesterday. 
  He was born in 1936 in the village of Govlar in the Tauzskiy 
region in the western part of the country. He graduated from 
the faculty of history of the Azerbaijan State University. He 
is a doctor of history, is married and has four children. 
  I joined the democratic movement five years ago at its very 
inception, Ahmedov said. Many who have been taught the Turkic 
traditions by myself are among the members of the party. 
  The professor believes that Abulfaz Elchibey and Iskander 
Hamidov are the most respectable politicians of Azerbaijan. 
  After Iskander Hamidov's resignation from the post of 
minister of interior, I became his close confidant and supporter 
in the Boz Gurd movement. 
  The theme of his masters' dissertation was Azeri-British 
relations in the 16th century. It dealt with the policy of 
England in the East during the first half of the 17th century 
(the beginning of England's colonial policy) the slogan of 
Bahdiyar Akhmedov is -- children must take care [sentence 
incomplete as received] 

</TEXT>

