<H3> <TI>   Explosion at University in Diyarbakir; 16 Wounded </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bomb in Cafeteria </H4>
<F P=102> TA2912163493 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1515 GMT 29 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> TA2912163493 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Dec 29 (AA) -- Sixteen people were 
wounded in bomb explosions in Southeastern Diyarbakir Province 
on Wednesday. 
  AA was told that the incident happened when two bombs 
planted 
in Dicle University cafeteria by the outlawed separatist 
terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization exploded 
wounding the students and school personnel and destroying the 
building. 
  Terrorists planted the bombs into garbage cans. 

</TEXT>

