<ABS>  FOUO </ABS>
<DATE1>   7 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governor Gives `Terrorist' Casualty Figures for 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2512190793 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 25 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> TA2512190793 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Unal Erkan, state of emergency region governor, has 
declared that 1,700 terrorists were killed and 540 were captured 
alive during operations conducted this year. Erkan added that 
240 organization members surrendered to the security forces. 
  In a statement to TRT in Diyarbakir, Erkan announced that 
17,000 persons were caught and referred to judicial authorities 
during operations against the collaborators of the terrorist 
organization in populated areas. Noting that a total of 1,200 
citizens, 135 of them women and 151 children, were killed in the 
organization's attacks against innocent and defenseless people, 
the regional governor remarked that 1,564 others were injured in 
these incidents. According to Erkan, this year security forces 
seized 4,000 weapons, 3,000 of them rifles, approximately 
500,000 rounds of ammunition of various types and calibers, 164 
rocket launchers, 1,500 rockets, 2,000 hand grenades, as well as 
large quantities of explosives, antiaircraft ammunition, and 
mortars. 

</TEXT>

