<H3> <TI>   Bomb Scare on Plane at Gatwick Airport </TI></H3>
<H4>   Crisis Over; Passengers Leave Plane </H4>
<F P=102> LD2412223593 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 2224 GMT 24 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2412223593 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Roger Williams and Rebecca Maer, Press Association] </F>
  [Text] Nearly 170 passengers on a holiday jet were caught 
up in an apparent hijack-bid drama tonight when a man on board 
claimed he had a bomb in his briefcase. 
  The Airbus A320 charter plane was on its way from Athens to 
Gatwick Airport when the man warned he had a bomb. 
  A spokesman for the airline, Excalibur -- an independent 
charter company based at East Midlands Airport -- said the 
details of how the man made his threat known were unclear. 
  "There is no longer a threat -- there was no bomb," the 
Excalibur spokesman said. "The passengers are leaving the plane." 

</TEXT>

