<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes in Northern Ireland After Ceasefire Ends </TI></H3>
<H4>   Some Casualties </H4>
<F P=102> LD2712011893 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 0109 GMT 27 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2712011893 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Ian Graham, Press Association in Belfast] </F>
  [Text] A bomb exploded in Northern Ireland early today -- 
just minutes after the midnight end of the IRA's Christmas 
ceasefire. 
  The bomb went off in the Co [county] Tyrone village of 
Fintona at 12:16 a.m., said the Royal Ulster Constabulary. 
  A spokesman said there were believed to be casualties after 
the fire brigade sent to the scene called for an ambulance. 
  The target of the bombing was not known but was thought to 
be 
the local police station, which was closed at the time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

