  Berlin BER 93-253, Madrid MAD 93-359 and Luanda LUA 93-357 
(29 Dec)--Lima bomb attacks kill two. 
<H5>  Philippines </H5>
  Johannesburg JOH 93-476 (27 Dec)--Report on "two bomb 
explosions." 
<H5>  Russia </H5>
  Moscow MOS 93-5944 and MRT 93-499 (23 Dec)--First 
broadcast is correspondent's report on schoolchildren taken 
hostage in Rostov-on-Don, second is video report on helicopter 
departing. 
  Moscow MOS 93-5947, 93-5948, Madrid MAD 93-353, Berlin BER 
93-245, Paris PAR 93-706 and Hamburg HAM 93-271 (24 
Dec)--Updates on hostage crisis; first broadcast shows task 
force, two released teenagers. 
  Moscow MOS 93-5949, 93-5950 (25 Dec) and 93-5951 (26 
Dec)--Updates on hostage situation from Mineralnyye Vody, crisis 
HQs. 
  Moscow MOS 93-5953, Tehran TEH 93-359, Johannesburg JOH 
93-475, Berlin BER 93-248, and Paris PAR 93-710 and 711 (26 
Dec)--Moscow's correspondent interviews witnesses, officials, 
released children; shots of crisis HQs. Paris runs reports on 
last hostages' release. 
  Madrid MAD 93-356, Hamburg HAM 93-273, Havana HAV 93-334, 
Berlin BER 93-249, and Paris PAR 93-712 and 93-713 (27 Dec)--End 
of hostage crisis. 
  Moscow MOS 93-5952, 93-5945 (27 Dec)--Correspondent's 
reports on kidnappers' arrest show weapons, ransom money, 
arrestees, operational briefing from officials. 
  Havana HAV 93-335 (28 Dec)--Kidnappers arrested. 
  Moscow MRT 93-504 and MOS 93-5955 (28 Dec)--Video shows 
official meeting helicopter pilots. 
<H5>  South Africa </H5>
  Johannesburg JOH 93-473 (24 Dec)--Explosion derails Soweto 
commuter train (1 min). 
  Johannesburg JOH 93-478 (29 Dec)--Three bombs explode in 
Port Elizabeth apartments (1 min). 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  Madrid MAD 93-352 (23 Dec)--Basque minister says 60 
percent of ETA prisoners favor ending armed struggle. 
<H5>  United Kingdom </H5>
  Havana HAV 93-335 (28 Dec)--Terrorist incidents in 
northern Ireland. 
<H5>  Venezuela </H5>
  Caracas CAR 93-492 (28 Dec)--Shots of three men implicated 
in car bomb case. 
<H5>  Former Yugoslavia </H5>
  Zagreb ZAG 93-358 (25 Dec)--Bomb planted in Serbian 
Orthodox church in Karlovac causes severe damage. 
<H5>  Zaire </H5>
  Kinshasa KIN 93-1159 (26 Dec)-Report on magistrate 
Lubuma's assassination. 

