<H3> <TI>   September Hijacker Sentenced to 9-Year Prison Term </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701095794 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0701095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Excerpt] A district court has sentenced a mainland Chinese 
man to nine years in prison and his wife to six for hijacking a 
mainland airliner to Taiwan last September. 
  The Taoyuan District Court meted out the prison terms for 
taxi driver Yang Ming-te and his wife Pan Feng-ying after 
finding them guilty of air piracy. The couple said that they 
would appeal. 
  Judge Chiang Hsiao-pei said that the court showed leniency 
to 
Yang because he surrendered [words indistinct]. His wife 
received the shorter term because she was only an accomplice, 
Qiang added. 
  The couple could have been sentenced to death. 
  The couple armed with a knife and fake explosives brought 
their son along when they hijacked the Russian-built Tupelov 154 
run by the mainland Sichuan Airlines to Taiwan on September 30 
and asked for political asylum. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

