Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Attorney General's Office announced tonight [4 
January] that on 31 December in Ocosingo, approximately 200 
heavily armed members of the group that has risen up in arms 
attacked Mexican Petroleum's [Pemex] RSS-6 exploration brigade, 
from whom they stole 1,566 kg of dynamite, 10,440 detonators, 
and the truck used to transport the explosives. The Attorney 
General's Office says there is evidence the explosives may have 
been used to destroy bridges in La Virgen and La Florida, 15 and 
13 km from Ocosingo respectively. 

