<DATE1>   12 January 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Firearms Factories Discovered in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112161893 Cairo AL-AKHBAR in Arabic 22 Dec 93 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> NC3112161893 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AKHBAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Badr al-Alfi] </F>
  [Excerpt] During the extensive police hunt for outlaws, 
especially those involved in black terrorism, the Cairo 
Intelligence Directorate discovered two factories that produce 
various types of firearms in al-Sharabiyah, one of the hotbeds 
of crime in the capital. 
  Interior Minister Major General Hasan al-Alfi authorized 
generous rewards for the officers involved and the citizens who 
gave information about the two factories. Twenty rifles and 
revolvers, as well as weapons parts, and assembling machines 
were found. The owners confessed to Major General Mansur 
'Isawi, assistant interior minister for Cairo security, and 
Major General Mahmud Wajdi, director of the General Intelligence 
Directorate, that they sold weapons to outlaws at very high 
prices. The prosecution ordered that they be remanded and the 
two factories closed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

