<H3> <TI>   Saddam Reportedly Ensnares, Kills Opposition Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601103994 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0912 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 6 Jan (KUNA) -- AL-WATAN newspaper today 
reported that Iraqi President Saddam Husayn has committed a new 
massacre against leaders from the Ba'th party who broke away 
from him years ago and sought refuge in Damascus. 
  The paper pointed out that Iraqi intelligence prepared a 
plan 
to lure a number of Iraqi opposition leaders living in Syria to 
the Kurdish area and from there to Mosul, where they were left 
to contact active elements of the [Iraqi] opposition; then they 
were arrested. The paper added that the plan succeeded and that 
death sentences were carried out on at least 10, including 
Muhammad al-Tai, who was described as a member of the dissident 
Iraqi regional command. 
  Sources of the dissident Iraqi regional command leadership 
in 
Damascus remained silent, but AL-WATAN paper reported these 
sources as saying that al-Tai acted individually and without 
orders from the leadership. 
  The paper said it was announced in Mosul that the bodies of 
five victims have been received, and that the rest are believed 
to have been killed during interrogation. 

</TEXT>

