Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Moti Amir] </F>
  [Excerpts] The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] today complied 
with the request of Fatah leaders in the Gaza Strip, and in the 
context of the understandings reached with them, released the 
five armed terrorists who were arrested in two incidents 
yesterday. [passage omitted] 
  Palestinian sources noted that the five are members of 
(al-Tanzim al-Siri), a secret organization of Fatah usually used 
for internal killings. 
  Processions and rallies were held today to mark the 29th 
anniversary of the establishment of Fatah. One rally, in 
Palestine Square, turned into a riot during which six locals 
were wounded by soldiers' gunfire, including a 60-year-old 
woman. A youngster who threw an explosive charge at the 
soldiers was also shot and wounded in the leg. 
  Thirty-five-year-old 'Azzam al-Aymuni was murdered in Hebron 
this morning. He was shot dead while walking in Hebron's 'Isa 
neighborhood. His body was taken to the forensic institute. He 
was apparently murdered on suspicion of being a collaborator. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1600 GMT on 2 January 
adds that "two firebombs were thrown at a fuel tanker in Hebron. 
The bombs shattered on the road. Soldiers escorting the tanker 
opened fire at the perpetrators, but they fled the scene."] 

