<H3> <TI>   Security Arrests Two in Sidon Shop Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Arrestees Suspected in Two Bombings </H4>
<F P=102> NC3112071293 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0615 GMT 31 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3112071293 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] According to available 
information, the security agencies in Sidon have apprehended a 
person who was wounded trying to throw an explosive charge at a 
shop in Darb al-Sim in eastern Sidon. A person helping him was 
killed in the explosion. 
  In the north, a person was caught in Tripoli and another was 
caught in Funaydiq in 'Akkar. Both are suspected of blowing up 
a shop in al-Zahriyah, Tripoli. The security agencies are 
interrogating the apprehended persons, 30 in all, mostly 
Lebanese and Palestinians. Contacts are under way with 
officials in the 'Ayn al-Hulwah Palestinian camp to hand over 
some suspects who are inside the camp. 
  Deputies who visited the president of the republic yesterday 
have cited him as saying that he has instructed the security 
agencies to step up efforts to uncover the circumstances 
surrounding recent explosions, particularly the blowing up of 
the Phalangist Party's central headquarters and the explosions 
that occurred in Tripoli. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

