<H3> <TI>   Security Arrests Two in Sidon Shop Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Suspects Confess to Five Incidents </H4>
<F P=102> NC3112205793 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 2015 GMT 31 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3112205793 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A security source announced this evening that the 
Lebanese and Syrian security agencies in the north arrested a 
network involved in explosions in Tripoli and its suburbs. Two 
of the network members, Marwan 'Ali Mir'i from al-Qalamun and 
Jihad Kamal Khalil from Tripoli, admitted that they carried out 
the following operations: Blowing up a shop in al-Bahsas on 31 
October, blowing up a shop in al-Tall in al-Kurah Square on 10 
December, blowing up a shop on al-Jummayzat Street in Tripoli on 
14 December, blowing up (?the Windiz) shop in al-Mina on 23 
December, and blowing up a shop in al-Zahriyah in Tripoli on 28 
December. The authorities concerned are pursuing the 
investigations to uncover all those involved. 

</TEXT>

