<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes at Italian Shoe Store in St Petersburg </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0501093994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 5 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM0501093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Sergey Krayukhin report: "Russo-Italian Store Bombed"] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg -- Unknown bombers marked the new 
year with explosions in the very center of St. Petersburg. 
  A powerful shock wave blew out a wall at the city's 
well-known "Marcopizzi" Italian shoe store, incinerating the 
display stands. The entrance hall at next door's 
"Petrogradskaya" subway station was also affected. It was only 
by good fortune that nobody was injured during this "firework 
display." 
  Criminal proceedings have been instituted. The search for 
the bombers has not yet yielded any results. 

