<H3> <TI>   Statistics on Suspects, Weapons Seized in Izmir in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0701164994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0701164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] During operations conducted against terrorist 
organizations in Izmir last year, security forces captured 366 
terrorists together with large quantities of weapons and 
ammunition. Of these terrorists, 237 were formally arrested by 
the Izmir State Security Court. 
  According to information received from the Izmir Security 
Directorate, during these operations, antiterrorist teams seized 
30 rifles, 49 pistols of various calibers, 1,575 rounds of 
ammunition, 95 hand grenades, 90 fuses, 14 hand-made bombs, 36 
dynamite sticks, one 300-cm-long time fuse, and 36 kg of 
chemicals used in the manufacturing of bombs. Also seized 
during the operations were four hand radios, three photocopy 
machines, two duplicating machines, four typewriters, two pairs 
of binoculars, and one computer. 

