<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six `Terrorists,' Including 2 Syrians, Killed in Southeast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0701165294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1450 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0701165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanliurfa, Dec 7 (AA) -- Security forces killed six 
terrorists, including two Syrian citizens in a clash in 
southeastern Turkey today. 
  AA learned that security forces on an operation early today 
in the Zeytindagi region of Suruc township, came across a group 
of terrorists. A clash erupted between the security forces and 
the terrorists who responded with fire to the calls of 
surrender. Of the six terrorists killed, three were women. 
  Two hide-outs were found in the same operation. 
  The terrorist organization is responsible for the deaths of 
more than 10,000 people in the region since 1984, when it 
launched a bloody campaign against the Turkish state and people. 
  The two Syrian terrorists are named Mezit Muhammet Ismail 
and 
Binevs (nickname--Dilan). 
  Officials said that woman terrorist Dilan was a bloody 
militant and was being searched for for a long time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
